person_credits.name: Hunt Emerson
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: The Medabots anime series on Fox Kids, is now available as manga! This series takes off with the super-charged battling adventures of a group of kids and their unique, high performance pet robots, the Medabots! Fueled with artificial intelligence and a specialized arsenal of unique weapons, Medabots compete against each other in exciting Robattles. In this first volume, Ikki dreams of becoming a champion Medafighter and competing in the World Robattle Tournament. But first, he has to get a Medabot. Ikki eventually does manage to get his own, but Metabee is a ten year old model and hardly listens to a thing Ikki says, but does help Ikki to foil a couple of thieves from robbing Ikki of his Rare Medal.
name: A Boy and His 'Bot!!

volume.name: What Dr. Freud Didn't Tell You

person_credits.name: Pat Oliphant
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: What Those People Need Is a Puppy!

description: Set in the exciting North American frontier this tale of a rescued dog and its loyalty and help to its new master really underlines the old saying that a dog is a man's best friend.
name: The Dog Crusoe

description: Our 5th compilation for Comixology of Aces Weekly - the award-winning on-screen comic art magazine featuring some of the world's finest creators of comic art. Published by David Lloyd, the guy who brought you V For Vendetta.
name: Volume 05

description: Spider-Man escapes! But what does he remember?
Spider-Man is once again a blank slate. Can the people of New York help him remember his true self before the villains recapture him?
Who Am I? rockets towards its conclusion.
Will Spider-Man remember his true self before its too late?

The cult horror sensation reaches its devastating conclusion, with the darkest chapter of all. Their search for the truth behind Emily's disappearance has pushed Hellinger to the brink of insanity and left Fiona in terrible danger. Now, everyone will find what they've been looking for... and will wish they hadn't. Features a cover by rising star artist Cody Schibi!

name: Black Dog

description: King Tut's plan to turn all Gothamites into mindless zombies reaches into the Gotham Police department. Meanwhile, Batman and Robin find themselves pushed into an early grave!
name: Chapter Forty-Eight

description: Themistocles' rage.
name: Vol. 3

description: Harper Connelly finds dead people for a living, but not everyone appreciates her special gift. In the stunning conclusion to this three-part series, Harper's step-brother, Tolliver Lang, finds himself in trouble with the law while Harper struggles to clear his name.
name: Chapter Five

description:
The Assassination of Marat Petric

11th year of City War. Enter Marat Petric. Impact Terra. Security? Kerry Pasann? Mack? This is the world now. City War.
name: The Assassination of Marat Petric

description:
Psychoboy Goes To Washington

Psychoboy has been been fired from every job in existence and has nothing meaningful to contribute to society. So he does what anyone in that situation would do... he runs for Congress!
name: Psychoboy Goes To Washington

description: Rose struggles to remember her past and the incident at the clock tower, and comes to an important decision!

The Neulids

In the wake of the upheaval surrounding Deskerna's insurrection two employees have escaped Mephys with something secret and irreplaceable. In response the conglomerate's security division has sent two of its best killers to track down and erase the thieves from existence. Matters are complicated however by the fact that the hunters themselves are being pursued by two tenacious FBI agents for reasons unknown.

What follows is a fierce chase across the lonely deserts of the American landscape ending in one of its old and forgotten towns; a place swallowed by time itself. It is here; the Killers, the Agents and the thieves will confront one of Mephys' most terrible secrets and set off a chain of events that will shake reality to its core. Strange Days begins here.
name: The Neulids

description: The Endling's true origin is revealed at last.

The Good, The Bad, and The Bane

Endstone is the story of a family of stoners... beings who can wield or "rock" mysterious stones that grant unique powers.

Kyri Thunderhead is a simple, martial-arts-dealing deer from the forests of Pennsylvania. Her mate, Jon Montaine, is a powerful stoner with a sordid past. Their daughter, Colindra, is a terrible dragon with a flair for fashion. And Pablo Montaine, the old patriarch of the clan, is literally the skeleton in the family closet.

Together, and sometimes apart, they must keep the Banestone, and the evil god-like being that dwells within it, from destroying the world. But is it a world worth saving?
name: The Good, The Bad, and The Bane

description:
We, The Many

Still devoid of answers after the confrontation of Kreel in Docklands, Parker and Gabe consult the survivors from the truck.

We begin to get some answers as to what is transpiring and introduce a new villain, Snare.

Issue #3 represents an enlightening follow up to the introductory action of the first two books.

A tale about the collapse of government, the rise of corporate power and the dwindling value of traditional morality in a futuristic Melbourne City.
name: We, The Many

description:
The Time Of Her Life

In which Carol has never felt like this before.
name: The Time Of Her Life

description: The opening arc concludes as the kids save the day...but at what cost? Will Captain Stone ever be the same?!
name: Halloween Hijinx Part Three

description: Nocturnus confronts the murderer. Galahad confronts goons. It will end better for one of them than it will for the other.

Blazed and Confused Part II

Dirk battles the Dragon Claw Ninja Clan while Chloe and Zack track down a dangerous drug kingpin known as The Wolf.
name: Blazed and Confused Part II

description:
Applications / Lung

Xavier finds love via his smartphone, but what kind of connection is he really making with this dude? ALSO: Forces are pulling Mattie and Harvey's burgeoning romance apart. She's going to college and he's... in an iron lung.
name: Applications / Lung

description: The Dragon-Mage reveals himself, and the sisters find themselves facing a foe unlike anything they have faced before... one who can seemingly raise dead to fight by his side...

You've been conscripted into the Golden Age in all its glory with ALL-WINNERS COMICS! Captain America stops a plot against General Douglas MacArthur! The Human Torch foils a plan to freeze the English Channel! The Destroyer fights the forces of the Devil himself! Plus: the Sub-Mariner, the Whizzer and more! With such wartime villains as the Stone-Man Slayer, Doctor Togu the Vampire, the Mock Mikado and Doctor Crime - and little-known characters like the Black Avenger, Raffles the Cracksman and Slow Motion Jones - there's no way you can lose with this spectacular collection of Golden Age tales! Collecting ALL-WINNERS COMICS (1941) #5-8.

name: Volume 2

description:
What Goes Up

After the apparent eruption in the previous issue, Lieutenant Yates took the initiative to reconnoiter the event on the summit of Mount Ka'ala on Northwestern Range of Oahu. The scope of what has happened will reach across the entirety of Oahu. And several new faces will enter the scene as the story picks up where we left off - on the summit.
name: What Goes Up

description:
The Super Squad of Superheroes Movement

Totally Naked Man gets an invitation to join the Super Squad of Superheroes Movement, but Pepper Gold may have some objections. Meanwhile, Universium hungers.
name: The Super Squad of Superheroes Movement

description:
The Third Impact has come. As the unbelievably massive form of Ayanami towers over the Earth, the Instrumentality Project enters its last stages. While the world shudders in terror as it is engulfed in a sea of LCL, Shinji's consciousness merges with Lilith's, and he searches his memories for a final understanding of himself and the fate of humanity.

Chapter Titles

  • Stage 91: Where Light Returns
  • Stage 92: Birthday
  • Stage 93: Sea of Life
  • Stage 94: Palms
  • Stage 95: Thank You ∞ Goodbye
  • Last Stage: The Journey Begins
  • Extra Stage: Eden In Summer

Note: The digital edition (11/25/2014) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 14

description:
NOWHERE MAN is the winner of the Glyph Comics Award for Best Male Character. It was also nominated for Glyph Comic Awards for Best Artist and Best Cover.

The series has garnered Pick of the Week from Book Case TV and Editor's Pick from Ladies of the Round Table. The series continues with JACKED UP, BOOK 2 - the origin story fans have been waiting for.
name: Volume 2.2: Jacked Up

description: The multiverse chase continues as Agent Nick Morgan begins an unlikely alliance with his inept double from our Earth. After escaping the desolation of Gamma 1, the duo must steal fuel cells from an Ascendancy facility hidden deep within a frozen ice world. And that's when their luck runs out...

MY DINNER WITH JOSEPH

Look, no self-respecting artist would draw the cover for us. This issue is just that effed up.
name: My Dinner With Joseph

description:
Is This It?

What happens when you finally get what you want, but it turns out it wasn't what you wanted? For Pretentious Record Store Guy, where does he go after turning his back on his lifelong dream. The final issue of the 3 issue mini-series.

When you're Pretentious Record Store Guy, you're life is pretty much made in the shade right? You get to see all the cool shows, pick through all the good music and take home all the latest promos. Life is pretty good, right?

The key to being in a scene is to be seen, and nowhere is more important than in a record store, where the employees are cooler than you and know every big band a year before anyone else does -- welcome to the world of Pretentious Record Store Guy.
name: Is This It?

description:
You Think You're A Man

It’s wall-to-wall action and destruction as The Pride face off against the powerful and deadly Basher! With an innocent life hanging in the balance! Be here to see if the team can face their first major threat, or if they can even survive…
name: You Think You're A Man

description: Wonder Woman accepts a covert mission from Queen Hippolyta: infiltrate Apokolips, find a group of Amazons imprisoned there by Darkseid, and bring them home alive.
name: Dig For Fire Part 1

description:
Escape is impossible, but it's his only chance.

Held prisoner in Stalag-X, Joe Human is hated by all, branded a coward and a traitor. He thinks he has entered a madhouse . . . but he has no idea of what's in store.

For Joe has attracted the attention of the camp's sadistic alien researcher, Mengele, who finds Joe "interesting." The alien doctor's research will take Joe to the edge of madness and beyond.

The BIGGEST cliffhanger of all time!

Another Martian rocket crashes into the territory of the Komori, the outlaw clan of ninja bats. Will Tomoe’s husband convince them to set aside their differences with the shogun and team up against the alien threat? Meanwhile, Lord Noriyuki reveals the astonishing secret weapon he believes will win the war—you just have to see it to believe it!

From multiple Eisner Award–winning creator Stan Sakai!

Celebrating Usagi’s 30th anniversary!
Valentine is cornered by the Tenebrae in modern-day Paris. Yet, with a new friend, he begins to hatch a plan to revive Nell's memory.

Retake

Take Number Two and Action

Video Girl Ai is back in the real world with a new mission from her creator--make a man fall in love with her. Yota is the only man for Ai, so it's too bad that Yota has decided to think of Ai as his sister. To make her mission more difficult, Moemi and Takashi are having relationship problems, and Moemi naturally turns to Yota for comfort.
name: Retake

description:
Slamming the Door

The vampires have attempted to run Ethan out of town on several occasions now.

They have failed at every attempt.

Ethan is proving that he is up to the task of destroying the coven.

Unfortunately, he has also shown that he is likely, the greater monster.
name: Slamming the Door

description: The latest stop on Witch Hunter's lost odyssey through time is a September morning in Paris, 1791, not long past the dawn of the French Revolution. With no way of his own to get back to the present, he's forced to rescue an evil witch from Madame Guillotine and spirit her out of France in exchange for her sorcerous one-way ticket to the 21st century. He won't have to rescue her all by himself, though, as he'll have help from someone with a lot of experience in the matter...the legendary Scarlet Pimpernel!

He's the best there is at what he does - and Wolverine's not so bad, either. Writer Jason Aaron's (PUNISHERMAX, Scalped) acclaimed and character-defining Wolverine run concludes in this final volume! Joined by comics' top artists, Aaron puts Wolverine through a physical and emotional wringer as the feral hero wreaks vengeance on the Red Right Hand, the group that sent him to Hell - but the final twist in their horrific plan might shatter Wolverine's spirit completely! Then, Wolverine faces decades-old responsibilities when he defends Chinatown from drugs and dragons. And when Sabretooth and Mystique team up to wreak havoc in Japan, Wolverine must take on both the Yakuza and the Hand - and defend his loved ones from a legacy of pain! Guest-starring Gorilla-Man, Fat Cobra, and a literal who's who of Wolverine's friends and foes! Collecting WOLVERINE (2010) #10-20 and #300-304.
name: Vol. 4

volume.name: Wolverine by Jason Aaron: The Complete Collection

description:
“Giants”

In the biggest battle royale in history as WWE Legends of the past continue to brawl with WWE Superstars of today across a vast array of fantastic warzones. It’s the ultimate clash of the titans when the most colossal WWE Superstars throughout history find themselves forced to fight against each other – Kevin Nash, the Big Show, Vader, The Great Khali, Yokozuna, and Gorilla Monsoon. As Roddy Piper and Daniel Bryan attempt to navigate the carnage, two more giants enter the fray – the Phenom who is Undertaker goes head-to-head against one of the greatest legends in WWE history!
name: Legends, Part Two: Giants!

description:
From Dusk Till Death

In 1918, the bloody events of "All Undead On The Western Front" took place on a World War 1 battlefield.

Now, some 73 years later, on April 14 1991, the City of Angels has turned into the city of the undead. How, over the subsequent decades, the Zombie virus of 1918 managed to make its way to L.A. remains a subject of myth and wild speculation.

Zombie-International will be uncovering the truth in future episodes. So, for now, brace yourself for a spine-chilling episode featuring Ernesto Santana and his fight for survival.
name: From Dusk Till Death

description:
The Mothman Cometh!

Zombie Marge finds herself in the clutches of evil aliens from beyond the stars. Marge plays a central part in their plans to conquer Earth once and for all, despite the interference of the mysterious Mothman. Just who's side is he really on anyway? All this and the zombie apocalypse begins without Marge's help. Part one of "The Mothman Cometh" begins this issue, plus bonus features, an interview with the artist and pin ups by Daryll Collins, Jay Fosgitt, Rodney Fyke and Woodrow Hinton III.
name: The Mothman Cometh!
Die Suche nach dem Schatz im Sibersee

description:
A Child In The Forest

Tim is a ten-year-old boy living with his mother in an isolated village in the deep wild forest. He loves listening to the stories of his grandfather about the history of humanity and the end of the Western civilization (known as The Fall). He dreams to discover the world... not knowing that his fortunate star will very soon lead him to an unexpected adventure that is about to change his life... and the life of everyone on Earth!
name: A Child In The Forest

description: In this new Absolute edition by the team of writer Jeph Loeb and artist Tim Sale, Batman faces off against his most demented and wicked foes. Taking place on the most evil of holidays, Halloween, the Dark Knight confronts his deepest fears as he tries to stop the madness and horror created by Scarecrow, the Mad Hatter, the Penguin, Poison Ivy and The Joker. This slipcased hardcover collects BATMAN: MADNESS #1, BATMAN: GHOSTS #1, BATMAN: LEGENDS OF THE DARK KNIGHT HALLOWEEN SPECIAL #1 and CATWOMAN: WHEN IN ROME #1-6!
name: HC

description: Bill Gates has been called the sultan of software and the master of the modern PC. His wife, Melinda Gates, has dedicated her life to helping women in third world countries to improve the living conditions for women. Together, they head The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, an organization recognized for its humanitarian works. The graphic novel explores what motivates this power couple.
name: GN

volume.name: Agents of Change: Bill & Melinda Gates

description: ORIGINAL SIN tie-in! Jim Hammond, the original Human Torch, must reveal the Invaders' tragic original sin - and it traces all the way back to Hiroshima! Did the team make a fatal miscalculation by disobeying orders from on high, and will Japanese super heroine Radiance make them pay the ultimate price? Then, when the Torch's former sidekick, Toro, is kidnapped, the Invaders discover a devastating new threat! Toro's kidnapper now controls every single Deathlok in the Marvel Universe! And this enemy's control over artificial intelligence just might extend to the Torch! Can Namor, the Winter Soldier and the Torch save humanity from death by Deathlok? Is one of the 'band of brothers' a traitor? And what do Killraven and a Martian invasion have to do with everything? This one has it all! Collecting ALL-NEW INVADERS #6-10.
name: Volume 2

description: It's the chapter you never knew about the story you know by heart! Join Peter Parker as he takes his first steps toward finding his way in the world as Spider-Man! He sought revenge and found responsibility. From that night on, a new life began. Peter's not a hero - not yet - but he'll get there somehow. But what happens when Peter meets Clash, New York's newest menace? Clash is Spidey's biggest fan, but what started off as fun and games soon turns deadly serious - and Clash is about to become his first super villain! And as a classic Spidey villain joins in on the fun, J. Jonah's Jameson's crusade against Spider-Man kicks into overdrive, and Uncle Ben's secrets come to light! Dan Slott and Ramon Perez deliver a new spin on Spider-Man's first 60 days! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (2014) #1.1-1.5 and material from #1.
name: Volume 1.1

description: Over 100 years ago, the novel arrived and became a smash hit. Get in on the ground floor of the wonderful retelling of the tale of Anne and her wish to live a wonderful, exuberant life! An all-ages glimpse inside the pages of Lucy Maud Montgomery's tale of Anne. Heartbreak and hope fill the pages as Anne's life fills every nook and cranny of this illustrated collected edition.
name: TPB

description: Hey Bayside Boppers, looks like there's a big reward for the school club that brings nefarious Zack Morris to justice! Zack's been framed for defacing the Bayside Tiger, and now the hunt is on in this mash-up between Saved by the Bell and The Warriors, brought to you by the killer team of MK Reed and Joe Flood (The Cute Girl Network). Zack Moorrrriisss... Come out and plaayyayyy!

Thus Approaches the Behemoth

How much tragedy can a man's soul take? What happens when you give that man power of mythical proportions?
name: Thus Approaches the Behemoth

description: What could Betty & Veronica possibly love more than Archie? That's easy -- shopping! Available for the first time ever as a Graphic Novel, get ready to hit the mall for the shopping spree of the century with America's favorite BFFs Betty & Veronica! Begin your very own shopping spree with this newest addition to the Archie graphic novel library, collecting some of the funniest stories in Archie Comics history featuring Riverdale's resident super-shoppers! Shop 'till you drop in this hilarious new collection!
name: Archie & Friends All-Stars Series Volume 23
The Tale of the Lizard Baron Part The First (of Six)

description:
Nuggets

This deep fried anthology book kicks off with the direct sequel to the events of the last book with excellent art by returning artist Mat Nixon. Co-creator Bobgar Ornelas will also be returning to take BPC back to the old days with 2 prequel tales. Jon Lennon joins the team to bring you a short story too hot for solicits. To wrap it all up, Ray Wegner will display some sizzlin' sequentials that will change BPC forever!
name: Nuggets

description: Transformed by the Super-Soldier Serum from a 98-pound weakling into Captain America, Steve Rogers led the charge to liberate the world from the Axis powers! But before World War II's end, an accident left him frozen in suspended animation and his sidekick, Bucky, dead. The world turned on for decades - and when the Avengers finally resuscitated him, Steve Rogers was greeted by a world vastly changed. He was a man out of time, tormented by the death of his partner - but no less committed to the cause of fighting evil in all its forms! In this Epic Collection, Stan Lee and Jack Kirby bring you the rebirth of an American icon. The rebirth of Captain America! Collecting AVENGERS (1963) #4, and material from STRANGE TALES (1951) #114 and TALES OF SUSPENSE (1959) #58-96.
name: TPB

volume.name: Captain America Epic Collection: Captain America Lives Again

description:
When Chihiro's father passed away, Chihiro inherited Tsurumaruya, an old and well-established confectionary shop in Kyoto. While he didn't inherit a sweet-tooth, he does have a craving... for his loyal clerk and childhood friend, Katsumi. Will Katsumi satisfy Chihiro's needs, or will Chihiro be stolen away to Tokyo by Mori, an older man after Chihiro's heart and body?! The second half of Shimaji's delightful collection of tales contains not only the answer to this question, but also the story of a truly odd couple. Will their relationship develop into something resembling a family, or simply end in tears?

Contents

  • Cat's Love Chapter 1
  • Cat's Love Chapter 2
  • Cat's Love Chapter 3
  • Cat's Love Chapter 4
  • Ever Seen Part 1
  • Ever Seen Part 2
  • Shooting Star
  • Rabbit's Love
name: Vol. 1

description:
Reluctant Heroes

This is the very beginning. Where the amazing journey starts. Okira awakens with five other strangers in a remote laboratory, and soon realizes that she is not the same person.
name: Reluctant Heroes

description:
Ride Fast For Wyoming

In this premiere issue of Cowgirl Romances take a trip back in time to the romantic plains of the Wild West, where women defended the house and found romance under the stars...

Bandits prowled the Rimrock trails and no ranch was safe - Bess Sherman lamented a sad song for the man she couldn't marry in "Ride Fast For Wyoming". Sweet seventeen and still nobody's darling, she was the queen of the mesa, "Calamity Jane". Lift up your lips to the seducing smile of dashing Don Diego in "A Kiss For Captain Lobo". The runaways traveled a risky road followed by looted bank vaults and rifles of the law - their refuge ahead was a lawless hideout of a woman called Rose, the beautiful and mysterious keeper of the "Halfway House". An evil land-owner tries to evict new homesteader Molly Mason - will she steal her land like Molly's man in "Beneath the Outlaw Moon".

Cowgirl Romances combines country beauties, Western villains and good ol' fashioned gun fights. Join the real heroes of the homestead in battles against bandits and for the hearts of hunky cowboys.

Enjoy a nostalgic trip down memory lane with the best titles from the golden age of comics. Yojimbo Press has lovingly remastered these timeless classics with vivid color correction and image restoration.
name: Ride Fast For Wyoming
